data.name: Comforting Split Pea Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and nutritious split pea soup that's simple to make and packed with flavor.
detailedCookingInstructions: Rinse the split peas under cold water and set aside.
In a large pot, heat a splash of oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, carrots, and celery, saut√©ing for about 5 minutes until softened.
Stir in the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute until fragrant.
Add the rinsed split peas, vegetable broth, bay leaves, salt, pepper, and thyme to the pot. Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer uncovered for about 45-60 minutes, or until the peas are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove the bay leaves before serving. Optionally, blend with an immersion blender for a creamier texture.
